 This module introduces the `StaticArray`. A static array is a non empty array fix a fixed size.
We can check the size in compile-time and ensure that the array is about as fast as a usual (dynamic) array in run time.

@docs StaticArray, singleton, fromList, push, get, set, length, resize, toArray, map, indexedMap, toRecord, fromRecord

 This module contains the `Index` type which can be though of as a range type.
A value of type `Index n` is in between `0` and `n`.

This type will be replaced in compile type with an Int. Resulting in no performance loss.

@docs Index, range, first, last, fromModBy, fromLessThen, increase, decrease, toInt, setLength
@docs One, Two, Three, Four, Five, Seven, Eight, Nine, Ten, Twenty
@docs OnePlus, TwoPlus, FourPlus, FivePlus, EightPlus, TenPlus, TwentyPlus

 This module introduces the `Length` type. The length type is a integer but its value is known in compile time.
This way we can ensure that no index out of bounds error accures.

@docs Length, one, two, four, five, eight, ten, twenty
